gw.plugin.document.impl

Class DocumentProductionDispatcher

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.guidewire.pl.plugin.document.internal.BaseDocumentProductionDispatcher
      • gw.plugin.document.impl.DocumentProductionDispatcher
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    com.guidewire.pl.system.integration.plugins.internal.InternalPlugin, IDocumentProduction, InitializablePlugin, java.rmi.Remote

    public class DocumentProductionDispatcher
extends com.guidewire.pl.plugin.document.internal.BaseDocumentProductionDispatcher
implements IDocumentProduction
    This class is really an aggregation of the other ICCDocumentProduction implementations. The idea here is that the configuration of this plugin will contain information for how to map a particular document production request to a specific implementation (for example by mime type).

    bjohnson

      • createDocumentSynchronously

        public DocumentContentsInfo createDocumentSynchronously(IDocumentTemplateDescriptor templateDescriptor,
                                                        java.util.Map parameters,
                                                        Document document)
        Dispatch through to the createDocumentSynchronously method on the configured ICCDocumentProduction implementation
        Specified by:
        createDocumentSynchronously in interface IDocumentProduction
        Parameters:
        templateDescriptor - the descriptor which should be used to create the new document
        parameters - An optional Map of name->object pairs which may be used either to create the document or perform extra operations (such as mailing the resulting document to recipients). May be empty or null.
        document - An in/out parameter. Contains the metadata set up for the document so far, and which may be modified by the plugin implementation
        Returns:
        a DocumentContentsInfo object which contains the results of the document creation.
